Introduction


Tashannie (Korean: 타샤니) was a short-lived South Korean duo under World Music Entertainment that consisted of Yoon Mirae (Formerly Tasha) and Annie (Lee SooA). They debuted on August 3rd 1999 with the Album ‘Parallel Phropecys’ and disbanded in May of 2000. They briefly reunited for a special stage in December of 2002 on Yoon HyunDo’s Love Letter.
